discussion_comments.comment_body:
**nit(non-blocking):** I realize this code was copied over from an _existing_ file -- but should we try to fix these variable names to convey more semantic meaning than just `s` or `c` while we're in there?

For example:
```suggestion
    const selection = this.selection.value;
    if (selection) {
      for (let connection of this.state) {
        if (connection.source === selection.source && connection.index === selection.index) {
          this.selection.next(connection);
          break;
        }
      }
    }
```

